data.name: Ukrainian Beet Soup (Borscht)
data.quickTastyDescription: A vibrant and hearty beet soup, rich in flavor and packed with nutrients, perfect for any occasion.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large pot, heat the vegetable broth over medium heat.
Add the diced onions and cook for about 5 minutes until they are soft.
Stir in the grated beets, carrots, and potatoes, and allow them to cook for an additional 10 minutes.
Add the shredded cabbage, tomato paste, bay leaf, and season with salt and pepper. Stir well.
Pour in the remaining vegetable broth and bring the soup to a boil.
Reduce heat and let it simmer for 30 minutes until all vegetables are tender.
Remove the bay leaf, stir in the chopped dill, and adjust seasoning if necessary.
Serve hot, with a dollop of sour cream if desired.
